								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">This article is about balneotherapy resorts.  For balneotherapy itself, see <a href="Balneotherapy" title="Balneotherapy">balneotherapy</a>.  For other uses, see <a href="Spa_(disambiguation)" title="Spa (disambiguation)">Spa (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<table class="metadata mbox-small plainlinks" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png" width="37" height="40" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/55px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/73px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png 2x" /></td>
<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="">Look up <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/spa" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:spa">spa</a></b></i>, <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Spa" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:Spa">Spa</a></b></i>, or <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/SpA" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:SpA">SpA</a></b></i> in Wiktionary, the free dictionary.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Taj_Spa_4.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Taj_Spa_4.jpg/250px-Taj_Spa_4.jpg" width="250" height="201" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Taj_Spa_4.jpg/375px-Taj_Spa_4.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Taj_Spa_4.jpg/500px-Taj_Spa_4.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Taj_Spa_4.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="Ayurveda" title="Ayurveda">Ayurvedic</a> spa in <a href="Goa" title="Goa">Goa</a>, <a href="India" title="India">India</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The term <b>spa</b> is associated with water treatment which is also known as <a href="Balneotherapy" title="Balneotherapy">balneotherapy</a>. <a href="Spa_town" title="Spa town">Spa towns</a> or <a href="Spa_resort" title="Spa resort" class="mw-redirect">spa resorts</a> (including <a href="Hot_spring" title="Hot spring">hot springs</a> resorts) typically offer various health treatments. The belief in the curative powers of mineral waters goes back to prehistoric times. Such practices have been popular worldwide, but are especially widespread in Europe and Japan. <a href="Day_spa" title="Day spa">Day spas</a> are also quite popular, and offer various personal care treatments.</p>
